{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.13",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 13 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:1",
      "text": "“Behold, my eye has seen all this. My ear has heard and understood it.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:2",
      "text": "What you know, I know also. I am not inferior to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:3",
      "text": "“Surely I would speak to the Almighty. I desire to reason with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:4",
      "text": "But you are forgers of lies. You are all physicians of no value.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:5",
      "text": "Oh that you would be completely silent! Then you would be wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:6",
      "text": "Hear now my reasoning. Listen to the pleadings of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:7",
      "text": "Will you speak unrighteously for God, and talk deceitfully for him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:8",
      "text": "Will you show partiality to him? Will you contend for God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:9",
      "text": "Is it good that he should search you out? Or as one deceives a man, will you deceive him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:10",
      "text": "He will surely reprove you if you secretly show partiality.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:11",
      "text": "Won’t his majesty make you afraid and his dread fall on you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:12",
      "text": "Your memorable sayings are proverbs of ashes. Your defenses are defenses of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:13",
      "text": "“Be silent! Leave me alone, that I may speak. Let come on me what will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:14",
      "text": "Why should I take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in my hand?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:15",
      "text": "Behold, he will kill me. I have no hope. Nevertheless, I will maintain my ways before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:16",
      "text": "This also will be my salvation, that a godless man will not come before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:17",
      "text": "Listen carefully to my speech. Let my declaration be in your ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:18",
      "text": "See now, I have set my cause in order. I know that I am righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:19",
      "text": "Who is he who will contend with me? For then I would hold my peace and give up the spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:20",
      "text": "“Only don’t do two things to me, then I will not hide myself from your face:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:21",
      "text": "withdraw your hand far from me, and don’t let your terror make me afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:22",
      "text": "Then call, and I will answer, or let me speak, and you answer me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:23",
      "text": "How many are my iniquities and sins? Make me know my disobedience and my sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:24",
      "text": "Why do you hide your face, and consider me your enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:25",
      "text": "Will you harass a driven leaf? Will you pursue the dry stubble?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:26",
      "text": "For you write bitter things against me, and make me inherit the iniquities of my youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:27",
      "text": "You also put my feet in the stocks, and mark all my paths. You set a bound to the soles of my feet,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.13.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:28",
      "text": "though I am decaying like a rotten thing, like a garment that is moth-eaten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
